    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-16T17:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-16T17:16:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/508</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-16T18:00:00-04:16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 14, 6 p.m.; my March 3, 11 a.m. Reliable information is that
                    little or no progress has been made. Idea of conference still entertained by
                    Argentina but slight activity in promoting it. Probable that project will be
                    abandoned. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
